          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer via an oblique junction serving 2 properties with no change in grade along the inclined property connection sewer with no vertical bends. Also known as Standard or Twin or Dual Type A Property Connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
			<xs:enumeration value="Ramp Riser">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer via an oblique junction serving a single property where the property connection sewer incorporates either or both a section laid at a steeper grade and vertical bends. Also known as Type B Property Connection.</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Twin Ramp Riser">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer via an oblique junction serving 2 properties where the property connection sewer incorporates either or both a section laid at a steeper grade and vertical bends. Also known as Twin or Dual Type B Property Connection.</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
			<xs:enumeration value="Jump Up">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer via a vertical oblique junction serving a single property where the property connection sewer incorporates either or both a section laid at a steeper grade and vertical bends. Also known a Type C or Type D Property Connection.</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Twin Jump Up">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer via a vertical oblique junction serving 2-4 properties and incorporating a change in elevation of the property connection sewer via a vertical drop/jump up. Also known as Twin or Dual Vertical Riser, Type C or Type D Property Connection.</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Sloped into MS Base">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer into the base of a maintenance structure serving a single property with no change in grade along the property connection sewer and no vertical bends. Also known as Standard or Type A Connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Twin Sloped into MS Base">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer into the base of a maintenance structure serving 2 properties with no change in grade along the property connection sewer and no vertical bends. Also known as Standard or Type A Connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Ramp into MS Base">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer into the base of a maintenance structure serving a single property where the property connection sewer incorporates either or both a section laid at a steeper grade and vertical bends. Also known as Type B Connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Twin Ramp into MS Base">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer into the base of a maintenance structure serving  2 properties where the property connection sewer incorporates either or both a section laid at a steeper grade and vertical bends. Also known as Type B Connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Drop into MS Base">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer into the shaft of a maintenance shaft or via a drop entry into a maintenance hole and serving a single property. Also known as Vertical Riser, Type C or Type D Connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Twin Drop into MS Base">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Connection to the reticulation sewer into the shaft of a maintenance shaft or via a drop entry into a maintenance hole and serving 2 properties. Also known as Vertical Riser, Type C or Type D Connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Stub">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>Obsolete designation for a connection into a Maintenance Hole, which is no longer used and only retained for backwards compatibility</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Unknown">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Unknown type of property connection</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:enumeration>
      <xs:enumeration value="Other">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>Some other type of Connection not covered by the standard types</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:enumeration>
		</xs:restriction>
	</xs:simpleType>
